  "stimulus": "The inside of a funnel of height 10 inches has circular cross sections, as shown in the figure above. At height $h$, the radius of the funnel is given by $r = \\dfrac{1}{3}(3 + h^2)$, where $0 \\leq h \\leq 10$. The units of $r$ and $h$ are inches.",
